Plot.
Max Peterson is a globe-trotting techno-whiz who 
installs security systems on computers. He receives 
an anonymous gift: a phone which sends messages 
that enable him to win at a casino. Max soon finds 
himself pursed by hit men, the casino's security 
chief, and a CIA operative. Who's sending Max 
messages? Previous recipients of similar windfalls 
have ended up dead. After a couple of close scrapes, 
Max realizes he's in danger, so he tries to find 
out the root of the conspiracy - which seems to 
have access to every security camera in the world 
before he's the next victim. Why is this happening 
to him, and who can he trust?
